			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Pre-Elemental and Elemental Bards<a name="41658"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 24 04 6:33 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Healer group is easy (feed mana), but the MT group and the DPS groups are kinda tricky</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
Those days of feeding healers are long over. The only mana song now is Chorus of Marr, which should be covered by one or two bards depending on raid force positioning. More likely you might be assigned to clerics to give them a boost to resists with PoV.
<br />

<br />
For MT group there's no single answer. Possible aims might be:
<br />

<br />
DS
<br />
Charisma
<br />
AC
<br />
Haste
<br />
Resists
<br />

<br />
DS is normally a given. Zek + PoV works well, with Zek giving a nice atk boost too.
<br />

<br />
Charisma increases the chances of DI triggering. IMO its a must have on any boss mob with spiky damage output, but some people aren't believers.
<br />

<br />
AC in PoP helps way past the old soft caps, so you might sing AC based songs (e.g. nillipus) to boost AC further.
<br />

<br />
Some people go against giving the MT extra haste, on the basis that more haste -&gt; more ripostes -&gt; more damage on MT. If the mob doesn't hit especially hard then overhaste (muse if you have it, or vah shir if not) may be an option on the MT group. Check first though!
<br />

<br />
Personally I'd use Zek+PoV+Charisma, maybe twist in Amp to boost PoV's DS if you're singing isn't capped. If you want to twist 4 then add in nillipus.
<br />

<br />
DPS groups: 
<br />
Zek + Muse (or vah shir+Rizlonas if you don't have muse),  quite likely adding AE mana or resists if appropriate. I'd then throw in HoS to reduce resists if no other bard is on that.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Caveat: I've not raided much with my bard, others here have much more experiance<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /></span></td>
