				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Pre-Elemental and Elemental Bards<a name="41671"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 24 04 9:02 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">DPS groups: 
<br />
Zek + Muse (or vah shir+Rizlonas if you don't have muse), quite likely adding AE mana or resists if appropriate. I'd then throw in HoS to reduce resists if no other bard is on that.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
There is no reason to play WoVahShir if you have Rizlona's. Rizlona's has 30% overhaste component+15% nuke focus over WoVahShir's 25% overhaste.
<br />

<br />
DI is Divine Intervention. It's a cleric spell that has a chance of saving the tank from death if their hitpoints drop below 0. DI checks for charisma, the higher the charisma, higher the chance of success.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
