				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Pre-Elemental and Elemental Bards<a name="41696"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 24 04 10:07 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I rarely play Muse when I'm in the tank group, not for any argument regarding haste or ripostes, but because on raids it is a pain to twist four. Normally I restrict myself to simply Zek and PoV for ds/resists on trash, with bosses getting Zek, PoV, and Amp to increase PoV's resists and DS. If I'm feeling particularly lucky (or if the boss has no procs) I'll do Zek/PoV/Harmonic/Amp or just Zek/PoV/Harmonic [Harmonic being, Niv's Harmonic, a singing-based AC/magic damage rune]. Something like Nilipus is kind of useless, because the rune part of the song means that once damage is taken, the rest of the stat bonuses drops as well. Niv's Harmonic is also tenuous in this regard because any AEDD or proc is going to remove the buff as well.
<br />

<br />
 I've never been asked for charisma, but I'm not sure if that's because the tanks have their cha maxed (with the appropriate buff), or if it is because they do not know how much I can boost it until I offer to do so, as it was with Harmonic.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
