				<td colspan="2"><span>Since DX9 I can't even twist 4 songs reliably in an exp group anymore, let alone a raid.<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-6.gif" border="0" alt="Sad" hspace="2" /> I've basically given up and dropped to twisting 3 in all circumstances.  So assuming I don't need to do AE resists:
<br />

<br />
My usual MT Twist is Zek-Niv's-Veeshan, unless DI/CHA is being used.  We are still doing SSRA-level raiding (pre-VT) so DI is rarely necessary, the damage from mobs is just not that spikey most of the time.  If no other bards are present I'll drop Niv's for Marr.  I amp as missed notes allow.
<br />

<br />
If I'm in a DPS group, I usually do Zek-Riz-Marr.
<br />

<br />
If I'm in a mixed group, I wing it based on the group composition.</span></td>
