			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">DI is Divine Intervention. It's a cleric spell that has a chance of saving the tank from death if their hitpoints drop below 0. DI checks for charisma, the higher the charisma, higher the chance of success.</span></blockquote>That's not quite correct. DI has a chance of performing a CH on a tank if their HP falls below 15%, meaning if the tank gets to 16% and gets one rounded, he's toast, no DI chance. The charisma of the tank affects the chance of success, as does the cleric AA Unfailing Divinity, which also adds the chance of partial success, which heals 1500HP per level of UD.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
