				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Divine Intervention is listed as 'Death Save' and I'm quite certain that that applies when his HP hits 0, not when his HP hits 15%. I'll admit I have no experimental data to support in, but unless you can provide such data to support your own claim I think I shall believe what I seem to have seen in my own experience.</span></blockquote>My main is a cleric, and I deal with DI a lot. It fires when health drops below 15%. It's easy to test this out. Just get a cleric to DI you and let some mob beat you down below 15% (not sure if it works with duels). 
<br />
<a target="_new" href="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/forums/showthread.php?s=&amp;threadid=15584&amp;highlight=Divine+Intervention+15">http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/forums/showthread.php?s=&amp;threadid=15584&amp;highlight=Divine+Intervention+15</a>
<br />
Scroll down to JanSorensen's comments. He has done the most research into DI and UD of any cleric.
